Badminton events at the 2019 African Games took place between 22â€“29 August at the Ain Chock Indoor Sports Center in Casablanca, Morocco. The badminton program in 2019 included men's and women's singles competitions; men's, women's and mixed doubles competitions alongside a mixed team event throughout the 8 days of competition. The tournament serves as a qualifier for the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, Japan.


